---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const title = 'RTMify Template Documentation: How to Use the Requirements Traceability Template';
const description = 'Complete guide to filling in the RTMify requirements traceability template. Field-by-field reference for User Needs, Requirements, Tests, and Risks tabs. Covers AS9100, ISO 13485, DO-178C, IEC 62304, ISO 26262, and ASPICE.';
const canonical = 'https://rtmify.io/docs/';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'RTMify', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Docs', url: '/docs/' }
];

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "TechArticle",
      "@id": "https://rtmify.io/docs/#article",
      "headline": "RTMify Template Documentation: How to Use the Requirements Traceability Template",
      "description": "Complete guide to filling in the RTMify requirements traceability template. Covers User Needs, Requirements, Tests, and Risks tabs for AS9100, ISO 13485, DO-178C, IEC 62304, ISO 26262, and ASPICE.",
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "RTMify", "url": "https://rtmify.io" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Iron Brothers Ventures, LLC", "url": "https://rtmify.io" },
      "datePublished": "2026-03-12",
      "dateModified": "2026-03-12",
      "proficiencyLevel": "Beginner",
      "dependencies": "Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets",
      "about": [
        { "@type": "Thing", "name": "Requirements Traceability Matrix" },
        { "@type": "Thing", "name": "Regulatory Compliance" }
      ],
      "isPartOf": { "@type": "WebSite", "name": "RTMify", "url": "https://rtmify.io" }
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowTo",
      "@id": "https://rtmify.io/docs/#howto",
      "name": "How to create a requirements traceability matrix with RTMify",
      "description": "Four steps to go from blank template to audit-ready RTM.",
      "step": [
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "position": 1,
          "name": "Download the template",
          "text": "Download the free .xlsx file from rtmify.io. No account, no email."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "position": 2,
          "name": "Fill in your data",
          "text": "Populate the four tabs: User Needs, Requirements, Tests, and Risks. Add IDs, descriptions, and cross-references."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "position": 3,
          "name": "Run RTMify Trace",
          "text": "Drop the .xlsx on RTMify Trace. It runs locally.  Nothing is uploaded."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "position": 4,
          "name": "Get your RTM",
          "text": "Download a full traceability matrix as PDF, Word, or Markdown. Requirements to tests to risks, fully resolved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "RTMify", "item": "https://rtmify.io/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Docs", "item": "https://rtmify.io/docs/" }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---

<DocsLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical={canonical}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  activeSlug="docs"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-[#1A1A2E] text-white py-16 px-4 -mx-4 sm:-mx-6 lg:-mx-8 mb-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6" style="font-family: var(--font-family-display);">
        Template Documentation
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        The RTMify template is a single .xlsx file with four tabs (User Needs, Requirements, Tests, Risks) that satisfies the traceability requirements of AS9100, ISO 13485, DO-178C, IEC 62304, ISO 26262, and Automotive SPICE. This documentation explains every field, every status code, and how to fill it in for your standard.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Start Section -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-8" style="font-family: var(--font-family-display);">
      Quick start
    </h2>
    <ol class="space-y-6 list-none">
      <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[#1A1A2E] text-white font-bold text-sm">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-[#1A1A2E] block mb-1">Download the template.</strong>
          <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm">Free .xlsx file. No account, no email. <a href="/download" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">Download it here.</a></p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[#1A1A2E] text-white font-bold text-sm">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-[#1A1A2E] block mb-1">Fill in your data.</strong>
          <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm">Populate the four tabs: <a href="/docs/user-needs/" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">User Needs</a>, <a href="/docs/requirements/" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">Requirements</a>, <a href="/docs/tests/" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">Tests</a>, <a href="/docs/risks/" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">Risks</a>. Add your IDs, statements, and cross-references.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[#1A1A2E] text-white font-bold text-sm">3</span>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-[#1A1A2E] block mb-1">Run RTMify Trace.</strong>
          <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm">Drop the .xlsx on <a href="/trace" class="text-[#1A1A2E] underline hover:no-underline">RTMify Trace</a>. It runs locally.  Your data never leaves your machine.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[#1A1A2E] text-white font-bold text-sm">4</span>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-[#1A1A2E] block mb-1">Get your RTM.</strong>
          <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm">Download a full requirements traceability matrix as PDF, Word, or Markdown. Requirements traced to tests, linked to risks, fully resolved.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Standard Section -->
  <section class="mb-16 border-t border-[#DDDDDD] pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-family-display);">
      Which standard are you working under?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-[#555555] mb-8">The template works for all six. Each quick-start guide walks you through filling it in with the right vocabulary, ID conventions, and annotations for your regulatory context.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      <a href="/docs/for/as9100/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #1565C0;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#1565C0] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3" style="background-color: #1565C0;">AS9100</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Aerospace quality. §8.3 design controls.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/for/iso-13485/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #2E7D32;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#2E7D32] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3">ISO 13485</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Medical devices. §7.3 design controls, ISO 14971.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/for/do-178c/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #6A1B9A;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#6A1B9A] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3">DO-178C</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Airborne software. HLR/LLR, DAL A–E.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/for/iec-62304/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #BF360C;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#BF360C] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3">IEC 62304</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Medical device software. Safety class A/B/C.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/for/iso-26262/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #E65100;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#E65100] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3">ISO 26262</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Automotive functional safety. HARA, ASIL.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/for/aspice/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline" style="border-left: 4px solid #004D40;">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-bold text-white bg-[#004D40] px-2 py-1 rounded mb-3">ASPICE</span>
        <p class="text-[#555555] text-sm m-0">Automotive SPICE. SYS.2/SWE.1–6 process evidence.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Four Tabs Section -->
  <section class="mb-16 border-t border-[#DDDDDD] pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-8" style="font-family: var(--font-family-display);">
      The four tabs
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <a href="/docs/user-needs/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">User Needs</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">Top of the traceability chain. Stakeholder needs, voice of customer, operational concepts, regulatory inputs. Every downstream artifact traces back here.</p>
        <p class="text-[#888888] text-sm m-0 mt-3" style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono);">Columns: ID · Statement · Source · Priority · RTMify Status</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/docs/requirements/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">SHALL statements. One per row, uniquely identified, independently verifiable. Each requirement links up to a User Need and down to a Test Group.</p>
        <p class="text-[#888888] text-sm m-0 mt-3" style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono);">Columns: ID · Statement · User Need ID · Priority · Test Group IDs · Lifecycle Status · Notes · RTMify Status</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/docs/tests/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">Tests</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">Test groups and individual test cases. Each Test Group maps to one or more requirements. Each test is typed as Verification or Validation and assigned a method.</p>
        <p class="text-[#888888] text-sm m-0 mt-3" style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono);">Columns: Test Group ID · Test ID · Test Type · Test Method · Notes · RTMify Status</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/docs/risks/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">Risks</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">Hazards and failure modes with severity-times-likelihood scoring, pre- and post-mitigation. Each risk links to the requirement that controls it.</p>
        <p class="text-[#888888] text-sm m-0 mt-3" style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono);">Columns: Risk ID · Description · Severity · Likelihood · Mitigation · Linked REQ · Residual Severity · Residual Likelihood · RTMify Status</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reference Section -->
  <section class="border-t border-[#DDDDDD] pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-8" style="font-family: var(--font-family-display);">
      Reference
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <a href="/docs/status-codes/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">Status Codes</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">
          What <code style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono); background: #F5F5F5; padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.8125rem;">OK</code>,
          <code style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono); background: #FEF9C3; padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.8125rem;">NO_TEST_LINKED</code>, and
          <code style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono); background: #FEE2E2; padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.8125rem;">UNRESOLVED</code> mean. What triggers each status. How to fix it.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/docs/traceability/" class="block p-5 border border-[#DDDDDD] rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A2E] m-0 mb-2">The Traceability Chain</h3>
        <p class="text-[#555555] m-0 text-base">How the four tabs connect. Bidirectional traceability, suspect flagging, and impact analysis, explained for all six standards.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
